---
import content from '../content/en.json';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  content={content}
  pageTitle="Terms of Service — SoloBond"
  pageDescription="Terms of Service for the SoloBond app. Read about usage terms, liability, privacy, and your rights."
  canonicalPath="/terms"
>
  <article class="terms-page">
    <div class="terms-page__inner">
      <header class="terms-page__header">
        <h1 class="terms-page__title">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="terms-page__updated">Last updated: March 2026</p>
      </header>

      <div class="terms-page__content">

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>1. Scope and Provider</h2>
          <p>These Terms of Service (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern the use of the SoloBond mobile application (&ldquo;App&rdquo;) and related services.</p>
          <p>The App is operated by:</p>
          <address class="terms-address">
            Igor Baum<br />
            c/o IP-Management #8358<br />
            Ludwig-Erhard-Stra&szlig;e 18<br />
            20459 Hamburg<br />
            Germany
          </address>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:team@solobond.app">team@solobond.app</a></p>
          <p>By downloading, installing, or using SoloBond, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, you must not use the App.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p>SoloBond is a daily check-in app that allows users to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Perform a one-tap daily check-in</li>
            <li>Designate a trusted contact</li>
            <li>Trigger an automatic notification if a check-in is missed</li>
          </ul>
          <p>SoloBond is a lifestyle and routine-support application.</p>
          <p>SoloBond is <strong>not</strong>:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>An emergency service</li>
            <li>A medical device</li>
            <li>A monitoring system</li>
            <li>A guarantee of safety</li>
          </ul>
          <p>SoloBond does not actively monitor users in real time and does not guarantee that notifications will be delivered without delay or interruption.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
          <p>You must be at least 16 years old to use SoloBond.</p>
          <p>In jurisdictions where a lower minimum age applies (e.g., 13 under COPPA in the United States), the respective local threshold applies.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>4. User Account Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>You are responsible for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Maintaining the security of your device</li>
            <li>Keeping your login credentials confidential</li>
            <li>Ensuring that the trusted contact information you provide is accurate</li>
            <li>Obtaining consent from the trusted contact before adding their email address</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>5. Trusted Contact Function</h2>
          <p>By adding a trusted contact, you confirm that:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>You have obtained their prior consent</li>
            <li>You understand that they will receive email notifications if you miss a check-in</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Trusted contacts may unsubscribe at any time.</p>
          <p>We are not responsible for any actions, inactions, or responses of the trusted contact.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>6. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use SoloBond for unlawful purposes</li>
            <li>Attempt to reverse engineer or manipulate the App</li>
            <li>Interfere with system security</li>
            <li>Use the trusted contact feature for harassment or surveillance</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts immediately in cases of misuse, unlawful activity, or violation of these Terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>7. Service Availability and Offline Behavior</h2>
          <p>We strive to keep SoloBond available but do not guarantee uninterrupted or error-free operation.</p>
          <p>The service may be temporarily unavailable due to maintenance, updates, technical issues, or third-party provider outages.</p>
          <p>SoloBond supports offline check-ins. Check-in data is stored locally on your device and synchronized with our server when an internet connection is available. Escalation notifications are triggered based on server-side timestamps, not local device time. Offline check-ins are only recognized once successfully synchronized.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>8. Disclaimer &mdash; Not an Emergency Service</h2>
          <p>SoloBond is not a substitute for emergency services.</p>
          <p>The App does not guarantee detection of emergencies, health incidents, or dangerous situations.</p>
          <p>If you are in immediate danger, contact local emergency services (e.g., 112 in the EU, 911 in the US).</p>
          <p>Use of SoloBond is at your own risk.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>To the extent permitted by law:</p>
          <p>We are liable without limitation for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Intent (Vorsatz)</li>
            <li>Gross negligence (grobe Fahrl&auml;ssigkeit)</li>
            <li>Injury to life, body, or health</li>
          </ul>
          <p>In cases of slight negligence, liability is limited to foreseeable damages resulting from a breach of essential contractual obligations (cardinal duties).</p>
          <p>Liability for indirect or consequential damages is excluded to the extent permitted by law.</p>
          <p>For free users, liability is limited in accordance with the principles above. No additional compensation is owed unless required by mandatory law.</p>
          <p>If you have purchased Premium features, total liability is limited to the amount paid within the 12 months preceding the claim.</p>
          <p>Mandatory consumer protection rights remain unaffected.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>10. Free and Premium Tiers</h2>
          <p>Core features of SoloBond are available free of charge.</p>
          <p>Premium features may be offered as paid subscriptions in the future.</p>
          <p>All purchases are processed exclusively via the Apple App Store. Apple&rsquo;s terms and refund policies apply. Subscription price, billing cycle, and cancellation conditions are defined in the App Store listing at the time of purchase.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>11. Account Deletion and Termination</h2>
          <p>You may delete your account at any time within the App settings.</p>
          <p>Upon deletion:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your data is removed from the primary database immediately</li>
            <li>Automated backups may retain data for up to 7 days</li>
            <li>Your trusted contact will be notified that the connection has been removed</li>
            <li>Associated trusted contact data will be deleted</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We may suspend or terminate accounts in cases of serious misuse or violation of these Terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>12. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>The name &ldquo;SoloBond&rdquo;, the App&rsquo;s logo, design, code, and branding are the property of Igor Baum. You may not copy, modify, distribute, or create derivative works without prior written permission.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>13. Privacy</h2>
          <p>Please refer to our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details on how we collect, use, and protect your data. The Privacy Policy forms an integral part of these Terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>14. Force Majeure</h2>
          <p>We are not liable for failure or delay in performance caused by events beyond our reasonable control, including but not limited to outages of third-party service providers, internet disruptions, natural disasters, or governmental actions.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>15. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the Federal Republic of Germany.</p>
          <p>If you are a consumer residing in the European Union, you also benefit from mandatory consumer protection provisions of your country of residence.</p>
          <p>Where legally permissible, the place of jurisdiction is Hamburg, Germany.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>16. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>We may update these Terms if the App or legal requirements change.</p>
          <p>Material changes will be communicated via the App or email where possible.</p>
          <p>If you do not agree to updated Terms, you may discontinue use and delete your account.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>17. Severability</h2>
          <p>If any provision of these Terms is found invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions remain unaffected.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
          <h2>18. Contact</h2>
          <address class="terms-address">
            Igor Baum<br />
            c/o IP-Management #8358<br />
            Ludwig-Erhard-Stra&szlig;e 18<br />
            20459 Hamburg<br />
            Germany
          </address>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:team@solobond.app">team@solobond.app</a></p>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .terms-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-xl));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-white);
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .terms-page__inner {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: var(--section-padding-x);
  }

  .terms-page__header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }

  .terms-page__title {
    font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 2.75rem);
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .terms-page__updated {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Section Blocks */
  .terms-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .terms-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .terms-section h2 {
    font-family: 'Plus Jakarta Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.5rem);
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    padding-top: var(--space-sm);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }

  .terms-section:first-child h2 {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  /* Body text */
  .terms-section p {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }

  .terms-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Lists */
  .terms-section ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .terms-section li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }

  .terms-section li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.75em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  /* Links */
  .terms-section a,
  .terms-address a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(232, 120, 92, 0.3);
    transition: text-decoration-color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .terms-section a:hover,
  .terms-address a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* Address blocks */
  .terms-address {
    font-style: normal;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }

  /* Strong emphasis */
  .terms-section strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-dark);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .terms-page {
      padding-top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-lg));
      padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }
  }
</style>
